\]

But energy is mass times length squared over time squared, so:

\[
\frac{\text{mass} \cdot \text{length}^2/\text{time}^2 \cdot \text{time}}{\text{length}^2} = \frac{\text{mass}}{\text{time}}
\]

Which matches the units of \( \frac{dM}{dt} \). So, the units are consistent. Phew!

