\begin{equation}
\delta m = 2.5 \log \left( \frac{L_{TOT}}{L_{sun}} \right) = 2.5 \log 10^6 = 15.
\end{equation}
Since the Sun has absolute magnitude +5, the magnitude of the cluser is $\boxed{-10}$.

