Angular resolution is given by the formula:

\[
\theta = \frac{\lambda}{D}
\]

where \(\theta\) is the angular resolution, \(\lambda\) is the wavelength, and \(D\) is the diameter of the telescope (or in this case, the maximum separation of the antennae). 

So, plugging in the values:

\[
\theta = \frac{10 \text{ cm}}{36 \text{ km}}
\]

