Then, factoring out \( C \):

\( C (3 + 3 i) = 4 A \)

So, \( C = \frac{4 A}{3 + 3 i} \). Multiplying numerator and denominator by \( 3 - 3 i \):

\( C = \frac{4 A (3 - 3 i)}{9 + 9} = \frac{4 A (3 - 3 i)}{18} = \frac{2 A (3 - 3 i)}{9} = \frac{2 A}{3} (1 - i) \)

Yes, that seems correct. So, the final expression for \( z_p(t) \) is:

\( z_p(t) = \frac{2 A}{3} (1 - i) e^{i t} \)

